# Prompt:
#   Execute the improvement plan at tools/title-loop/docs/21-f1e3c51/improvement-plan.md.
#   
#   Modify lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts and any related files as needed.
#   Make sure:
#   1. All existing tests still pass
#   2. The CLI at tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts still works
#   3. The code is clean and follows the project conventions in AGENTS.md
#   4. No unnecessary changes outside the title extraction logic
#   
#   CRITICAL CONSTRAINT: Do NOT modify the substring deduplication logic in title-extractor.ts.
#   The block starting with "// Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter"
#   must remain exactly as-is. It keeps the SHORTER candidate. Do not invert this to keep the longer.
#   This has been incorrectly changed 5 times and breaks tests every time.
#   
#   After making changes, run: npx vitest run --globals lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts
#   Fix any test failures before finishing.

============================================================

All 33 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented from the improvement plan:

**`lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`:**
- **Pattern F** (burst exemption): ALL_CAPS lines are never skipped by `findBurstEnd`, preventing `BARSZCZ` from being eaten as garbled OCR
- **Pattern C2** (prose prologue): New detection block skips 3+ consecutive body-text lines at document start (lowercase-starting, continuation-ending, or sentence-ending with 5+ words)
- **Pattern G** (subtitle suppression): Short mixed-case title at position 0 (≤5 words) triggers a −0.15 penalty on longer mixed-case candidates at positions 1–2
- **Pattern H1** (compound variant): When result is `"A : B"` and both sides share the same first word, returns only `A`
- **Pattern I** (NFC normalization): Output goes through `.normalize("NFC").trim()`

**`tools/title-loop/title-loop.py`:**
- **Pattern B** (OCR normalization): Added `_ocr_normalize` (`0→o`, `1→i`, `€→e`) applied in `titles_match`
- **Pattern I** (Unicode normalization): `normalize()` now applies NFC and strips NBSP/BOM before comparison

Changes A, C1, D, F (vowel threshold) were already implemented in the previous iteration.
