{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AnwdEk4uFF3aoRha2f6J91","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my search, here's what I found in the title-loop.py file:\n\n## Found Functions in `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py`\n\n### 1. `normalize` (Line 111)\n```python\ndef normalize(s: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Normalize whitespace, hyphens, and case for comparison.\"\"\"\n    return \" \".join(s.lower().replace(\"-\", \" \").split())\n```\n\n### 2. `_strip_diacritics` (Line 129)\n```python\ndef _strip_diacritics(s: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Strip Polish diacritics to ASCII equivalents.\"\"\"\n    return s.translate(_POLISH_DIACRITICS)\n```\n\n### 3. `titles_match` (Line 134)\n```python\ndef titles_match(extracted: str, expected: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Binary match: does the extracted title contain all expected title parts?\n    Expected may contain multiple titles separated by '+'.\n    Normalizes hyphens→spaces and strips Polish diacritics for robustness\n    against generated filenames that use kebab-case or drop diacritics.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not extracted:\n        return False\n    extracted_norm = _strip_diacritics(normalize_separators(normalize(extracted)))\n    expected_parts = [\n        _strip_diacritics(normalize_separators(normalize(p)))\n        for p in expected.split(\"+\")\n    ]\n    return all(part in extracted_norm for part in expected_parts)\n```\n\n### Notes:\n- **`_ocr_normalize` function**: Not found in the codebase. It doesn't appear to exist in either the Python or TypeScript files.\n- **`unicodedata` import**: Not found. The file does not import `unicodedata`. Instead, it uses a translation table `_POLISH_DIACRITICS` (defined at line 120) to handle diacritics conversion.\n\nThe diacritics mapping is defined just before `_strip_diacritics`:\n```python\n_POLISH_DIACRITICS = str.maketrans(\n    \"ąćęłńóśźżĄĆĘŁŃÓŚŹŻ\",\n    \"acelnoszzACELNOSZZ\",\n)\n```"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adb0dbcc84ceb5c36 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 92694\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 32090</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5bfc1c9-4aac-4af0-806b-8a2590b8aad5","uuid":"fcf76c38-1341-49c5-899d-cb691527622f","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py and find the `titles_match`, `normalize`, `_strip_diacritics`, and `_ocr_normalize` functions. Show me their complete implementations. Also look for any `unicodedata` import. Return the line numbers and full code of these functions.","agentId":"adb0dbcc84ceb5c36","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my search, here's what I found in the title-loop.py file:\n\n## Found Functions in `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py`\n\n### 1. `normalize` (Line 111)\n```python\ndef normalize(s: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Normalize whitespace, hyphens, and case for comparison.\"\"\"\n    return \" \".join(s.lower().replace(\"-\", \" \").split())\n```\n\n### 2. `_strip_diacritics` (Line 129)\n```python\ndef _strip_diacritics(s: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Strip Polish diacritics to ASCII equivalents.\"\"\"\n    return s.translate(_POLISH_DIACRITICS)\n```\n\n### 3. `titles_match` (Line 134)\n```python\ndef titles_match(extracted: str, expected: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Binary match: does the extracted title contain all expected title parts?\n    Expected may contain multiple titles separated by '+'.\n    Normalizes hyphens→spaces and strips Polish diacritics for robustness\n    against generated filenames that use kebab-case or drop diacritics.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not extracted:\n        return False\n    extracted_norm = _strip_diacritics(normalize_separators(normalize(extracted)))\n    expected_parts = [\n        _strip_diacritics(normalize_separators(normalize(p)))\n        for p in expected.split(\"+\")\