{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016w1VJ3JfQcYqf7VyDYVUD7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of what needs to be done. Let me look at what's already implemented in title-extractor.ts vs. what still needs to be done from the plan:\n\n### Already implemented in title-extractor.ts:\n1. Pattern A: trailing page number filter (`/\\s{3,}\\d{1,4}\\s*$/.test(text)`) ✅\n2. Pattern C1: SECTION_LABELS expansion (serving suggestion, glaze, for the sauce, etc.) ✅\n3. Pattern C1: ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS expansion ✅\n4. Pattern C1: \"For the...\" filter ✅\n\n\n5. Pattern D: bracket filter ✅\n6. Pattern D: METADATA_PATTERNS (PORCJI, PORTIONS, CZĘŚĆ, PART) ✅\n7. Pattern F: vowel ratio at 0.10 ✅\n8. Pattern F: The burst detector is checking for ALL_CAPS exemption by examining the findBurstEnd function, which iterates through lines looking for short text entries...\n\nExamining the burst detection logic...\n\nStill needs implementation:\n1. Pattern F (partial): ALL_CAPS exemption in `findBurstEnd`\n2. Pattern C2: Prose prologue detection in `findBurstEnd`\n3. Pattern B (Python): OCR char normalization in `titles_match`\n4. Pattern I (Python): Unicode NFC normalization in `normalize` + fix invisible chars\n5. Pattern I (TS): NFC normalization in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` output\n6. Pattern E: Title case normalization\n7. Pattern G: Subtitle suppression bonus\n8. Pattern H: Compound variant handling\n\nLet me look more carefully at the current title-extractor.ts file to understand what's already implemented. Looking at the return statement around line 965, I see it's just joining the selected text without any normalization or title case conversion. There's no `toTitleCase` function defined, no subtitle suppression logic, and no compound variant handling in the file yet. So I still need to add NFC normalization, title case conversion, subtitle suppression, and compound variant handling to the return statement, plus implement the ALL_CAPS and prose prologue patterns in `findBurstEnd`.\n\nFor title-loop.py, I need to add OCR character normalization in the `titles_match` function and Unicode NFC normalization plus invisible character handling in the `normalize` function. Let me run the tests first to see where things stand currently.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":821,"cache_read_input_tokens":61685,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":821},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5bfc1c9-4aac-4af0-806b-8a2590b8aad5","uuid":"29307bc4-11cf-4e6c-81b2-bf21c1047145"}
