{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XfiMH9NVi96bVu2amcDuzC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 33 tests pass. Now let me implement the remaining changes. Let me do them one by one.\n\nThe changes needed based on my analysis of what's already in the file vs. what the plan prescribes:\n\n**Already implemented in title-extractor.ts:**\n1. Pattern A: trailing page number ✅\n2. Pattern C1: SECTION_LABELS expansion ✅\n3. Pattern C1: ALWAYS_BLOCK_JOIN_LABELS expansion ✅\n4. Pattern C1: \"For the...\" filter ✅\n5. Pattern D: bracket filter ✅\n6. Pattern D: METADATA_PATTERNS additions ✅\n\n\n7. Pattern F: vowel ratio at 0.10 ✅\n\n**Still needed in title-extractor.ts:**\n1. Pattern F: ALL_CAPS exemption in `findBurstEnd` while condition\n2. Pattern C2: Prose prologue detection\n3. Pattern I (TS): NFC + .trim() on return\n4. Pattern E: Title case normalization (toTitleCase)\n5. Pattern G: Subtitle suppression \n6. Pattern H1: First-variant extraction from compound title (H3 via CZĘŚĆ/PART already done)\n\n**Still needed in title-loop.py:**\n1. Pattern B: `_ocr_normalize` + use in `titles_match`\n2. Pattern I (Python): Unicode NFC + NBSP/BOM stripping in `normalize`\n\nNow I'm modifying the `findBurstEnd` function to skip ALL_CAPS lines when checking for garbled text, then I'll move through the remaining patterns in both files.\n\nAdding prose prologue detection... I see the issue now - I need to add a separate prose prologue detection block that runs after the cooking instruction check, both wrapped in their own `if (i === 0)` conditions so they don't interfere with each other. The prose prologue detector should scan forward and skip any consecutive lines that look like body text before we start looking for the actual title. I need to handle the case where cooking instructions don't match—then the prose prologue detection should kick in instead. Both `if (i === 0)` blocks won't run simultaneously since the first one will set `i` if it finds cooking verbs, preventing the second from executing. Now I'm adding normalization patterns for the text processing: applying NFC normalization and trimming whitespace on the returned strings, plus implementing title case conversion for consistency.\n\nBut I'm realizing this title case logic might conflict with existing tests that expect all-caps output, so I should verify what the test suite actually expects before making this change.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1157,"cache_read_input_tokens":62506,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1157},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5bfc1c9-4aac-4af0-806b-8a2590b8aad5","uuid":"dbd37e27-0282-4e5b-972f-8acab807e428"}
