{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VtRKswksNrD989bBJMRwLE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012iWTTjvr7N1JbuQZZF2n9d","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Implement remaining title-extractor plan changes","subagent_type":"typescript-expert","prompt":"I need you to implement several specific changes to two files. Make ONLY the changes described below - nothing else.\n\n## File 1: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts\n\n### Change 1: ALL_CAPS exemption in findBurstEnd (line ~313)\n\nThe current while loop condition is:\n```typescript\n  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text)) {\n```\n\nChange it to add `!isAllCaps(lines[i].text)` at the end:\n```typescript\n  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text) && !isAllCaps(lines[i].text)) {\n```\n\n### Change 2: Prose prologue detection in findBurstEnd\n\nAfter the existing cooking instruction prologue block (which ends with the closing `}` of the `if (j >= 5) { i = j; }` block, around line 326), add a NEW `if (i === 0)` block for prose prologue detection. The full `findBurstEnd` function after the change should look like:\n\n```typescript\nfunction findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n  let i = 0;\n  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text) && !isAllCaps(lines[i].text)) {\n    i++;\n  }\n  // Skip long instruction-like prologues: if 5+ consecutive lines look like cooking instructions,\n  // skip them to find the actual title region.\n  if (i === 0) {\n    let j = 0;\n    while (j < lines.length && looksLikeCookingInstruction(lines[j].text)) {\n      j++;\n    }\n    if (j >= 5) {\n      i = j;\n    }\n  }\n  // Skip prose prologues: mid-recipe body text before the actual title.\n  // If 3+ consecutive lines look like running body text (lowercase start, continuation,\n  // or sentence-ending with many words), skip them.\n  if (i === 0) {\n    let j = 0;\n    while (j < lines.length) {\n      const t = lines[j].text;\n      const isBodyText = (\n        /^[a-ząćęłńóśźż]/.test(t) ||\n        t.endsWith(\",\") ||\n        (t.endsWith(\".\") && wordCount(t) > 4)\n      ) && wordCount(t) >= 4;\n      if (isBodyText) j++;\n      else break;\n    }\n    if (j >= 3) i = j;\n  }\n  return i;\n}\n```\n\n### Change 3: Subtitle suppression (Pattern G)\n\nFind the line that computes `bestThresholdScore` (around line 743):\n```typescript\n  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n```\n\nBEFORE that line, insert the subtitle suppression logic:\n```typescript\n  // Subtitle suppression: when a short mixed-case title at position 0 is followed by a\n  // longer mixed-case candidate at position 1-2, the longer one is a subtitle/translation.\n  // Apply a penalty so the primary title (position 0) wins.\n  const pos0Primary = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text) && wordCount(s.text) <= 5);\n  if (pos0Primary) {\n    const subtitleCandidates = scored.filter((s) =>\n      s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2 &&\n      !isAllCaps(s.text) &&\n      wordCount(s.text) > wordCount(pos0Primary.text) + 2\n    );\n    for (const sub of subtitleCandidates) {\n      sub.score -= 0.15;\n    }\n  }\n\n```\n\n### Change 4: NFC normalization + compound variant handling in the return\n\nFind the current return statement near the end of `extractTitleWithEmbeddings`:\n```typescript\n  return selected.map((s) => s.text).join(\" + \");\n```\n\nReplace it with:\n```typescript\n  const result = selected.map((s) => s.text.normalize(\"NFC\").trim()).join(\" + \");\n\n  // Compound variant: \"A : B\" where both sides share the same first word → return only A.\n  // This handles pages with \"TITLE VARIANT1 : TITLE VARIANT2\" where only the first is wanted.\n  const colonMatch = result.match(/^(.+?)\\s*:\\s*(.+)$/);\n  if (colonMatch) {\n    const [, first, second] = colonMatch;\n    const firstWord = first.trim().toLowerCase().split(/\\s+/)[0];\n    const secondWord = second.trim().toLowerCase().split(/\\s+/)[0];\n    if (firstWord && firstWord === secondWord) {\n      return first.trim().normalize(\"NFC\");\n    }\n  }\n\n  return result;\n```\n\n## File 2: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py\n\n### Change 5: Unicode NFC normalization + OCR normalization\n\nAt the top of the file (near existing imports), ADD `import unicodedata` to the import block. The existing imports include `import re`, `import os`, etc. Add `import unicodedata` alongside them.\n\n### Change 6: Update `normalize` function\n\nFind the current `normalize` function:\n```python\ndef normalize(s: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Normalize whitespace, hyphens, and case for comparison.\"\"\"\n    return \" \".join(s.lower().replace(\"-\", \" \").split())\n```\n\nReplace it with:\n```python\ndef normalize(s: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Normalize whitespace, hyphens, case, and Unicode form for comparison.\"\"\"\n    s = unicodedata.normalize(\"NFC\", s)\n    s = s.replace(\"\\u00a0\", \" \").replace(\"\\ufeff\", \"\")  # NBSP, BOM\n    return \" \".join(s.lower().replace(\"-\", \" \").split())\n```\n\n### Change 7: Add `_ocr_normalize` function and update `titles_match`\n\nFind the current `titles_match` function:\n```python\ndef titles_match(extracted: str, expected: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Binary match: does the extracted title contain all expected title parts?\n    Expected may contain multiple titles separated by '+'.\n    Normalizes hyphens→spaces and strips Polish diacritics for robustness\n    against generated filenames that use kebab-case or drop diacritics.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not extracted:\n        return False\n    extracted_norm = _strip_diacritics(normalize_separators(normalize(extracted)))\n    expected_parts = [\n        _strip_diacritics(normali