{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RSfxkpRqqHbGRsqDVC8Dv3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 33 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented from the improvement plan:\n\n**`lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`:**\n- **Pattern F** (burst exemption): ALL_CAPS lines are never skipped by `findBurstEnd`, preventing `BARSZCZ` from being eaten as garbled OCR\n- **Pattern C2** (prose prologue): New detection block skips 3+ consecutive body-text lines at document start (lowercase-starting, continuation-ending, or sentence-ending with 5+ words)\n- **Pattern G** (subtitle suppression): Short mixed-case title at position 0 (≤5 words) triggers a −0.15 penalty on longer mixed-case candidates at positions 1–2\n- **Pattern H1** (compound variant): When result is `\"A : B\"` and both sides share the same first word, returns only `A`\n- **Pattern I** (NFC normalization): Output goes through `.normalize(\"NFC\").trim()`\n\n**`tools/title-loop/title-loop.py`:**\n- **Pattern B** (OCR normalization): Added `_ocr_normalize` (`0→o`, `1→i`, `€→e`) applied in `titles_match`\n- **Pattern I** (Unicode normalization): `normalize()` now applies NFC and strips NBSP/BOM before comparison\n\nChanges A, C1, D, F (vowel threshold) were already implemented in the previous iteration."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":316,"cache_read_input_tokens":79657,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":316},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5bfc1c9-4aac-4af0-806b-8a2590b8aad5","uuid":"179c4dec-e6c6-4da8-831e-c210a76b4966"}
